@AI5300 That kind of move in $AMAT and $KLAC definitely reflects strong AI infra expectations getting priced in fast. The key question isn’t whether demand exists, it’s how long capex growth stays above expectations before efficiency or digestion phases kick in. 
Even “unlimited spend” narratives tend to come in waves, with periods of acceleration followed by consolidation. Staying long can work, but timing the volatility around those waves is what usually separates smooth gains from drawdowns. 
I’m also watching this closely. If you want, I can share how I map AI capex cycles into entry and risk windows. Follow me if you’re interested, I can DM you the full breakdown

